                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Albany</placeName>\n                <date>18. December 5610</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your favour from the <date>13</date> inst. was<lb/>\n                <sic>duely</sic>\n                <sic>recieved</sic>, and I saw in it, that you enjoy a good<lb/> health, you are\n                always <sic>buissy</sic>, and that is all man can<lb/> ask for. No\n                    <sic>pecuniar</sic> profit, you say, can be made by<lb/> the publication of my\n                works, then it shall not be published,<lb/> for if it can not be sold, it is\n                certainly not worth to<lb/> be bought, then it is not worth to be published;\n                and<lb/> if it be sold, it must pay a little for the vast trouble<lb/> I will finish\n                it as good as I can and also as soon<lb/> as I can. My peculiar farce<add>?</add>\n                will I display in the<lb/> fourth maxim, which shall be entirely historically<lb/>\n                in conformity with the Prophets, and in many instances<lb/> explaining them. In this\n                fourth maxim I will share<lb/> the historical failure of <sic>christianity</sic> on\n                one side and<lb/> its unhistorical ground on the other side. About the<lb/>\n                <add>שם המפורש</add> have I to remark, that I can impossibly<lb/> alter the\n                expression in this part, which you have in<lb/> hand, as I take the name as a\n                foundation of the<lb/> Theology, in the other parts I do not intend to mention<lb/>\n                it. And after all I must remark, that the word<lb/>\n                <persName>Jehovah</persName> is quite an other expression, than that forbid<lb/>den\n                one. You write, that my style is not popular<lb/> enough, I tried my best to draw\n                the <sic>Philosophie</sic><lb/> from heaven down to the earth; but I can</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v11w60x/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
