                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v11w60x/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>2</p>\n            <p>not do it any better than I did; I have in the<lb/> following maxims no such high\n                object than in the<lb/> first, and can be more plain. If the works will not\n                find<lb/> a publisher in <placeName>America</placeName> I send it to\n                    <placeName>England</placeName>, or I<lb/> translate it in the <sic>german</sic>\n                language and send it to<lb/> my old home, where it will find plenty of friends.<lb/>\n                I have found a young man, that intends to finish<lb/> his education for the\n                    <sic>jewish</sic> ministry in my house,<lb/> and he will teach in my school,\n                wherefore you may<lb/> please to leave off the advertisement.</p>\n            <p>The society in <placeName>New York</placeName>, which publishes the <sic>jewish</sic><lb/>\n                <sic>cronicle</sic>, has received a new supply from\n                <placeName>England</placeName>,<lb/> a young convert, <persName>Joseph\n                    Levy</persName>, appointed to go to<lb/>\n                <placeName>New Orl.</placeName> paid me a visit, but I did not allow him to<lb/> sit\n                down in my house. The man is three fourth <sic>creasy</sic><lb/> and one\n                    <sic>forth</sic> an idiot. The <sic>jews</sic> in <placeName>Albany</placeName>\n                find a<lb/> great deal of difficulties in the project to build a new<lb/> Synagogue,\n                and I think they will not build.</p>\n            <p>You probably <sic>recieved</sic> a letter of one of my scholars,<lb/> in which he\n                wishes you to send the marks of the publication<lb/> society for our school-library;\n                the boy did not know<lb/> that you resigned the office of corresp. secrty.,\n                wherefore<lb/> I must beseech you to send him or me the proper<lb/> direction of the\n                present cor. sect. I am curious<lb/> to read what you will say about my views\n                on<lb/> our Theology, because I am sure, that if you<lb/> find fault you will say\n                it.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v11w60x/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
